Tenant & User Model Spec (Java Backend – Identity + Membership)

Scope

This document defines the identity, tenant membership, and session/token model for the Merchant Admin portal and backend APIs.

It locks:
	•	Users can belong to multiple tenants
	•	Tokens are scoped to one tenant per session
	•	Invite-by-link + reset-by-link workflows
	•	Access token TTL 15 minutes
	•	Refresh token TTL 14 hours
	•	Refresh token rotation enabled
	•	Security edge-case handling (membership disable, refresh reuse)

⸻

1) Principles

1.1 Separation of concerns
	•	User = global identity (email + password)
	•	Tenant = business account
	•	Membership = user’s role & status within a tenant

1.2 Tenant-scoped sessions

A user can have many memberships, but an access token always represents exactly one tenant context.

Switching tenants requires issuing a new tenant-scoped token.

1.3 Tokens are short-lived and safe for an internal portal
	•	Access token: 15 minutes
	•	Refresh token: 14 hours
	•	No “session expiring soon” alerts; users re-login when refresh expires.

⸻

2) Entities & Relationships

2.1 User

Represents a human user with login credentials.

Key properties:
	•	Unique email address
	•	Password hash (never store plaintext)
	•	Status (active/disabled)

2.2 Tenant

Represents a merchant business account (your customer).

Key properties:
	•	Tenant identifier
	•	Plan & features (used by authorization capability gating)

2.3 TenantMembership

Represents a user’s relationship to a tenant.

Key properties:
	•	Role: ADMIN / STAFF / EDITOR
	•	Status: INVITED / ACTIVE / DISABLED
	•	One membership per user per tenant (unique constraint)

⸻

3) Database Schema (Core Tables)

3.1 users

Purpose: global identities

Minimum fields:
	•	id (UUID, PK)
	•	email (TEXT, unique, normalized lowercase)
	•	password_hash (TEXT)
	•	status (ACTIVE, DISABLED)
	•	created_at, updated_at

Recommended indexes:
	•	unique index on email

3.2 tenants

Purpose: business accounts

Minimum fields:
	•	id (UUID, PK)
	•	name (TEXT)
	•	code (TEXT, unique) — used for SKU prefixes and human-friendly IDs (optional but recommended)
	•	plan (BASIC, MID, PRO)
	•	created_at, updated_at

3.3 tenant_memberships

Purpose: multi-tenant membership, roles

Minimum fields:
	•	id (UUID, PK)
	•	tenant_id (UUID, FK → tenants.id)
	•	user_id (UUID, FK → users.id)
	•	role (ADMIN, STAFF, EDITOR)
	•	status (INVITED, ACTIVE, DISABLED)
	•	created_at, updated_at

Constraints:
	•	unique: (tenant_id, user_id)

Indexes:
	•	(user_id) for “which tenants does this user belong to”
	•	(tenant_id) for “list tenant staff”

